- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes a clustering algorithm for detecting hardware Trojans. 
- cs.ET (Embedded Systems) is another possible category as hardware Trojans can be inserted into embedded systems. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses a method for generating test patterns to increase the transitions of suspicious Trojan logics. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is also less likely but still possible as the paper is about detecting hardware Trojans in circuits.
